{% if has_local_connection %}
Locally run on the board
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""

If you connected an HDMI monitor to your FPGA and a mouse and a keyboard
(both on one dongle), you can navigate the ADI Kuiper Linux that is on the
FPGA.

Going to the top left corner icon (the menu icon), search for IIO
Oscilloscope. Opening it will automatically connect to the setup and you
can use the application.
